Breeding adult.description: Western Meadowlarks have less white on the outer tail feathers than Easterns, but this difference can be hard to judge.

Female/nonbreeding male.description: Female and nonbreeding Bobolinks are smaller and slimmer, with much shorter bills and more uniform buff coloring than Eastern Meadowlarks.

Adult (Savannah).description: Savannah Sparrows are much smaller with a shorter bill and whitish, not yellow, underparts unlike the large and long-billed Eastern Meadowlark.
